cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with visual question answering, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a new loss function, which falls under the category of optimization and learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, since the task involves multimodal learning, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
